 NARRATOR: The
 duties of a small town

00:00:34.834 --> 00:00:37.133
 police officer never change.

00:00:37.234 --> 00:00:39.334
PRESTON: It's nice to
work in a smaller town,

00:00:39.434 --> 00:00:40.934
because you can have
the rapport with people

00:00:41.033 --> 00:00:43.334
and people can trust you.
OFFICER: Looks like a military..

00:00:43.434 --> 00:00:44.567
 NARRATOR: Patrol the streets,

00:00:44.667 --> 00:00:47.534
 collect the facts,
 find the crook.

00:00:47.634 --> 00:00:49.133
SPROCK: Everybody
knows everybody.

00:00:49.234 --> 00:00:52.267
And everybody's got an
opinion on what people do.

00:00:52.367 --> 00:00:54.133
 NARRATOR: Make
 people feel safe.

00:00:54.234 --> 00:00:55.300
 Nothing's changed.

